ODM chairman John Mbadi has promised aspirants fair nominations.He spoke at the national ODM Women Conference in Kisumu town on Thursday. Present were Cord leader Raila Odinga s wife Ida, Kisumu woman representative Rose Nyamunga, Busia s Florence Mutua and Nyamira s Alice Chae.Mbadi said the party has developed a strategy to divide the country into three zones. Zone A includes regions where the party does not enjoy a lot of support. Here, the party will select and give direct nominations.Zone B involves places where the party has an almost equal number of voters with the opponents. They will use delegates to elect a candidate. Zone C includes regions where the party is popular. Here, there will be universal suffrage.